We came here for the happy hour (because we couldn't afford the dinner menu) and it turned out to be a great experience. We originally came here because we saw it featured as one of the "best places for patio dining" and truly, the views were spectacular (although we couldn't sit outside since it was 110 degrees!). We ordered margaritas and for food the potato chips, quesadilla, and mini burgers. All were delicious and had generous portions. The staff was also very friendly and attentive.

