I love the newly remodeled Joint! Especially since I'm short, General Admission is not a fun option for me, however, the floor is tiered (so that even if you are in the back, you will still be about 2 feet higher than the people in front of you). We saw Linkin Park here and surprisingly, except for the pit area, the rest of the crowd was pretty respectful and not pushing even though it's still general admission floor. I can't complain about anything - great acoustics and really nice place to see a band!

